Set up runners:
  1. Review the .env created by herd init; add model/provider credentials there
     If .env is missing, copy .env.herd.example to .env first
  2. Confirm HERD_RUNNER_BOOTSTRAP_TOKEN is present in .env; do not overwrite it
  3. Run: claude setup-token (uses your subscription, no API cost)
     Add the token as CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN in .env
  4. docker compose -f docker-compose.herd.yml up -d

Enable workflows (after runners are ready):
  gh variable set HERD_ENABLED --body true --repo test-org/test-repo
  Workflows are installed but inactive until HERD_ENABLED is set.

Production orchestration:
  Herd dispatches jobs through the control plane and GitHub App installation auth.
  Do not add HERD_GITHUB_TOKEN or human PAT secrets for production workflows.

Next steps:
  herd plan          Start a planning session
  herd plan "..."    Start a planning session with an initial prompt
  herd status        Check system status
